    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS INTERNATIONAL PS125-9A, PS140-9A, PSO125-9A, PSO140-9A AND PSO150-9A - COUNTERSHAFT
        IDENTIFICATION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT IDENTIFICATION</title>
        <figure id="f1300562" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300562" filename="../figg13/G1300562.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 71. Gear Hub Direction</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">This view of the 13MAB countershaft shows the hub direction of the gears (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300562">Figure 62</hotlnk>). The gears are secured with three keys.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1300563" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300563" filename="../figg13/G1300563.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 72. Every Countershaft Gear in Line</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If a straight edge is placed between these teeth (painted here to show the timing marks),
                every gear on the countershaft will be in line (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300563">Figure 63</hotlnk>). When the shafts are in time, these marks will be directly
                across from each other.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
